&lt;h1&gt;TPD – Obstetrics and Gynaecology (Examinations and Learner Support)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An outstanding individual is sought to fulfill the role of Training Programme Director in Obstetrics and Gynaecology (Examinations and Learner Support). The Training Programme Director will work closely with the Director for Education and the RCOG in designing and implementing the changes to the MRCOG exam structure, to develop and deliver a comprehensive teaching and assessment package to support MRCOG examination preparation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have strong leadership and communication skills and be able to work effectively as members of a multi-professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts will be available on the basis of a secondment arrangement to HEE YH remunerated on the NHS Consultant Pay Scale – 0.75 PA per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All work undertaken is to be incorporated into the Consultant Job Plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Marina FlynnJob titleHead of School for Obstetrics and GynaecologyEmail addressMarina.Flynn@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
